From: Paolo Bonzini <pbonzini@redhat.com>
Date: Tue, 4 Feb 2020 15:26:29 -0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/6] KVM: nVMX: Don't emulate instructions in guest mode

commit 07721feee46b4b248402133228235318199b05ec upstream.

vmx_check_intercept is not yet fully implemented. To avoid emulating
instructions disallowed by the L1 hypervisor, refuse to emulate
instructions by default.

Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
[Made commit, added commit msg - Oliver]
Signed-off-by: Oliver Upton <oupton@google.com>
Signed-off-by: Paolo Bonzini <pbonzini@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
[OP: backport of ed9e97c35b4 from linux-4.19.y branch of linux-stable]
Signed-off-by: Ovidiu Panait <ovidiu.panait@windriver.com>
---
 arch/x86/kvm/vmx.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/x86/kvm/vmx.c b/arch/x86/kvm/vmx.c
index 1919e934a334..0452e3472a03 100644
--- a/arch/x86/kvm/vmx.c
+++ b/arch/x86/kvm/vmx.c
@@ -11454,7 +11454,7 @@ static int vmx_check_intercept(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu,
 	}
 
 	/* TODO: check more intercepts... */
-	return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
+	return X86EMUL_UNHANDLEABLE;
 }
 
 #ifdef CONFIG_X86_64
